******
[1] China: avian flu human H7N9 [Fujian]
Date: Sat 17 Jan 2015
Source: Medical Press [edited]
http://medicalxpress.com/news/2015-01-die-bird-flu-china.html


Two people have died of the H7N9 strain of avian flu in China's eastern province of Fujian, state media said Saturday [17 Jan 2015], quoting local health officials.

Fujian has confirmed 15 cases since the start of 2015, Xinhua news agency reported. It did not say when the 2 patients died.

Another human infection was reported in the adjacent province of Jiangxi on Fri [16 Jan 2015], Xinhua said, while both the municipality of Shanghai and neighbouring Zhejiang province have reported cases "this winter" [2014-15].

Cases of the virus accelerated in China in 2014, with statistics compiled by health authorities in Beijing showing 310 cases were diagnosed on the mainland from January until 10 Dec [2014], including 132 deaths. Another death was recorded on 29 Dec [2014]. In 2013, the country recorded 46 deaths and 144 cases since the outbreak started in March [2013] of that year.

