******
[2] China avian flu human H7N9 [Shandong, Jiangxi]
Date: Sun 18 Jan 2015
Source: FIC [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-18064.html


The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health (DH) is closely monitoring 2 additional human cases of avian influenza A(H7N9) in Shandong and Jiangxi.

According to the latest reports of the Mainland health authorities, the patient in Shandong is a 60-year-old man who worked in Jiangsu before onset of illness, while the patient in Jiangxi is a 34-year-old man who was hospitalised for treatment in critical condition.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[3] China avian flu human H7N9 [Shanghai, Guangdong]
Date: Sun 18 Jan 2015
Source: FIC [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-18064.html


The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health (DH) is closely monitoring 3 additional human cases of avian influenza A(H7N9) in Shanghai (one case) and Guangdong (2 cases).

According to the notification of the Health and Family Planning Commission of Guangdong Province, the 2 cases involved a 66-year-old man in Shenzhen who is currently in critical condition, and a one-year-old girl in Shanwei who had recovered.

And according to the latest report of the Shanghai Municipal Commission of Health and Family Planning, the patient in Shanghai is a 69-year-old man who is currently under treatment.

To date, 483 human cases of avian influenza A(H7N9) have been reported by the Mainland health authorities, respectively in Zhejiang (145 cases), Guangdong (123 cases), Jiangsu (63 cases), Shanghai (43 cases), Fujian (28 cases), Hunan (24 cases), Anhui (17 cases), Xinjiang (9 cases), Jiangxi (9 cases), Shandong (6 cases), Beijing (5 cases), Henan (4 cases), Guangxi (3 cases), Jilin (2 cases), Guizhou (one case) and Hebei (one case).

